		</header>
		<div class="flex flex-col gap-y-6">

			<h1 
				class=" border-neutral-700 font-ranade text-justify text-[5vw] leading-[5vw]  uppercase " 
				style="font-family: 'Gambarino-Regular';"
			>
				Max Georgopoulos Product designer & developer. Be design and engineering is artificial
			</h1>
			<div class="columns-2 md:columns-3 lg:columns-4 gap-3">
				<div class="bg-[#E4E4E4] p-3">
					<div class="h-80 w-80 bg-neutral-300"></div>
					<h3>Formie</h3>
					<p>Formie is a form builder for Figma. It's a plugin that lets you create forms in Figma, and then export them as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-[#E4E4E4] p-3 h-fit">
					<div class="h-60 w-80 bg-neutral-300"></div>
					<h3>Formie</h3>
					<p>Formie is a form builder for Figma. It's a plugin that lets you create forms in Figma, and then export them as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-[#E4E4E4] p-3">
					<div class="h-80 w-80 bg-neutral-300"></div>
					<h3>Formie</h3>
					<p>Formie is a form builder for Figma. It's a plugin that lets you create forms in Figma, and then export them as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-[#E4E4E4] p-3 rounded-lg">
					<div class="h-80 w-80 bg-neutral-300"></div>
					<h3>Formie</h3>
					<p>Formie is a form builder for Figma. It's a plugin that lets you create forms in Figma, and then export them as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
